{{move to Wiktionary}}A '''rubber chicken dinner''' is a colloquial name for formal dinners or events thrown by politicians to raise funds. The name derives from the fact that the quality of the food is secondary to the purpose of the event and seldom good.

In the [[Pantomime (theatre)|pantomime]] 'Never Trust a City Slicker', a dinner of soap soup is served with a rubber chicken.
